{{Infobox cricketer | name = Dennis A'Court | birthname=Dennis George A'Court | image = | caption = | batting = Right hand batsmen | bowling = Right arm fast medium | columns = 1 | column1 = [[First-class cricket|First-class]] | matches1 = 49 | runs1 = 420 | bat avg1 = 11.35 | 100s/50s1 = 0/0 | top score1 = 47* | deliveries1 = 9585 | wickets1 = 145 | bowl avg1 = 26.82 | fivefor1 = 5 | tenfor1 = 0 | best bowling1 = 6/25 | catches/stumpings1= 10/- | international = | country = | testdebutfor = | testdebutagainst = | testdebutdate = June 8 | testdebutyear = 1960 | lasttestdate = June 19 | lasttestfor = | lasttestagainst = | lasttestyear = 1963 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/27/27404/27404.html CricketArchive | date = | year = }}
'''Dennis George A'Court''' (born 27 July 1937) is a former [[Wales|Welsh]]-born [[cricket]]er. He was a right-handed batsman and a right-arm [[fast bowler|medium-fast bowler]] who played [[first-class cricket]] for [[Gloucestershire County Cricket Club|Gloucestershire]] between 1960 and 1963.<ref name="ca">{{cite web | url = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/27/27404/27404.html| title = Dennis A'Court | publisher = www.cricketarchive.com | subscription = yes| accessdate = 1 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=cricinfo>{{Cricinfo | id= 8662| name= Dennis A'Court| accessdate= 31 August 2017}}</ref> He was born in [[Markham, Wales|Markham]] in [[Monmouthshire (historic)|Monmouthshire]], a former mining village.
He took 145 first-class wickets, with a best of 6 for 25 against the [[South African cricket team in England in 1960|South African tourists]] in 1960: ''[[Wisden Cricketers' Almanack|Wisden]]'' noted that he "shocked the South Africans with his accuracy, liveliness, and disconcerting swing and movement of the ball".<ref>{{Cite book | title = [[Wisden Cricketers' Almanack]] | edition = 1961 | publisher = [[Wisden Cricketers' Almanack|Wisden]] | chapter = South Africans in England, 1960 | page = 287 }}</ref> He took five wickets in an innings on five occasions.<ref name=cricinfo/>
